<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-24T00:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-24T00:36:00-05:00" n="937" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d937">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13581.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Canova</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Aguascalientes</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-23T23:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 23, 1914, 11 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Replying to Convention’s telegram beseeching him to submit his
                            resignation, Carranza answers he will not do so; that he will deliver
                            the Executive Power only to the president who shall have been elected by
                            the people.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Canova</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>